Categories:
    value data type
    pointer data type
    reference data type


Value Data Types:
    int = whole numbers, 4bytes
    long = whole number, 8bytes
    float  = fractional (F at the end of number, ie: 100.50F), 4bytes, 6 - 7 decimal digits
    double = fractional (D at the end of number, ie: 100.50D), 8bytes, 15 decimal digits
    char = single letter, 2bytes
    string = reference type, but value type declaration, stores characters 2bytes per character
    boolean = true or false, 1bit